metadata:
  section_id: 16
  section_name: Chapter 16
  hadith_first: 1635
  hadith_last: 1767

hadiths[133]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
1635,"“A Muslim has six duties towards other Muslims: When you meet him, you should salute him; when he invites you, accept his invitation; when he asks for your advice, give it to him; when he sneezes and praises Allah, say May Allah have mercy on you; when he is ill, visit him; and when he dies follow his funeral.” Related by Muslim.",,,50752,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1636,"“Look at those who are lower than you (financially) but do not look at those who are higher than you, lest you belittle the favors Allah conferred upon you.” Agreed upon.",,,50753,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1637,"An-Nawwas bin Sam'an (RAA) narrated, ‘I asked the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) about virtue and sin and he replied, “The essence of virtue is (manifested in) good morals (Akhlaq) whereas sinful conduct is that which turns in your heart (making you feel uncomfortable) and you dislike that it would be disclosed to other people.” Related by Muslim.",,,50754,,Chapter 16
1638,"“When three of you get together in company, two of you must not talk privately while isolating the third, so as not to make him feel sad (that he is left out) till you mingle with other people (i.e. you are joined by others).” Agreed upon and the wording is from Muslim.",,,50755,"Ibn Mas’ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1639,“A man should not ask another man to get up from his place in order to take his seat. But you should make room for each other and spread out.” Agreed upon.,,,50756,"Ibn Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1640,"“When one of you eats, he must not wipe his hand till he licks it, or gives it to someone else to lick (such as a wife, husband, etc.).” Agreed upon.",,,50757,"Ibn Abbas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1641,"“The young should salute the old, the one who is passing by should salute the one who is sitting, and the small group of people should salute the larger one.” Agreed upon.",,,50758,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1642,"In a version by Muslim, “And the one who is riding should salute the one who is walking.”",,,50759,,Chapter 16
1643,"“When a group of people passes by, it is sufficient if one of them gives a salutation, and it is sufficient for those who are sitting that one of them replies.” Related by Ahmad and Al-Baihaqi.",,,50760,"Ali (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1644,"“Do not initiate the saluting of Jews and Christians (when you meet them), and if you meet any of them on the road, force him to go to the narrowest part of the road (i.e. do not give way for them to pass, but keep going). Related by Muslim.",,,50761,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1645,"“When one of you sneezes, he should say, ‘Alhamdulillah (Praise is to Allah) and his (Muslim) brother should say to him, ‘Yarhamuka Allah (May Allah have mercy on you). When he says this to him (the last phrase), he should reply, ‘Yahdikum Allah (May Allah guide you) and grant you well being.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50762,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1646,“None of you should drink while standing.” Related by Muslim.,,,50763,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1647,"“When one of you puts on his shoes, he should put on the right one first and when he takes them off, he should take off the left one first, so that the right one should be the first to be put on and the last to be taken off.” Agreed upon.",,,50764,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1648,"“None of you should walk with one shoe, but should either wear them both or take them both off” Agreed upon.",,,50765,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1649,“Allah will not look on the Day of Judgment at him who lets his garment drag on the ground out of pride and arrogance.” Agreed upon.,,,50766,"Ibn Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1650,"“When one of you eats he should eat with his right hand, and when he drinks he should drink with his right hand, for the devil eats and drinks with his left hand.” Related by Muslim.",,,50767,"Ibn Umar narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1651,"“Eat, drink, wear clothes and give sadaqah but with neither extravagance nor pride.” Related by Abu Dawud and Ahmad.",,,50768,"Amro bin Shu’aib narrated on the authority of his father, on the authority of his grandfather (RAA), that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1652,"“He who wishes to have his earnings grow (and be blessed) and his term of life prolonged, he should keep ties with his kin” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50769,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1653,“The one who severs the ties of kinship will not enter Paradise.” Agreed upon.,,,50770,"Jubair bin Mut'am (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1654,"“Allah has made it prohibited for you to be disrespectful (showing undutiful behavior) to your mothers, to bury your daughters alive, to refuse others (their dues), and to demand things from others (which are not worth demanding), and He hates that you engage in gossip, asking many questions about people’s affairs and wasting wealth.” Agreed upon.",,,50771,"Al-Mughirah bin Shu'bah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1655,"“Allah’s pleasure results from the parent’s pleasure, and Allah’s displeasure results from the parent’s displeasure.” Related by At-Tirmidhi. Ibn Hibban and al-Hakim graded it as Sahih.",,,50772,"'Abdullah bin 'Amro bin al-As (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1656,"“By Him in Whose Hand my soul is, a slave of Allah does not truly believe till he wishes for his neighbor what he wishes for himself.” Agreed upon.",,,50773,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1657,"Ibn Mas'ud (RAA) narrated, ‘l asked the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) “Which sin is the most serious?” He replied, attribute a partner to Allah, though He Alone has created you. “I asked, “What next?” He said, kill your child, fearing that he will share your food with you.” I asked again, “What next?” He said, “To commit adultery with your neighbor’s wife.” Agreed upon.",,,50774,,Chapter 16
1658,"“For a man to insult his parents, is one of the major sins.” It was asked, ‘Does a man insult his parents?’ He replied “Yes, he insults the father of a man who in return insults his father, and he insults a man’s mother who in return insult his.” Agreed upon.",,,50775,"'Abdullah bin 'Amro bin al-As (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1659,"“It is not permissible for a Muslim to shun his brother for more than three nights. When they meet, this one turns away (from that one) and that one turns away (from this one) and the best of them is the one who greets his brother first.” Agreed upon",,,50776,"Abu Aiyub (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1660,“Every act of goodness is (considered as) Sadaqah.” Related by Al-Bukhari.,,,50777,"Jabir bin ’Abdullah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1661,“Do not consider any act of goodness as being insignificant even if it is meeting your brother with a cheerful face.” Related by Muslim.,,,50778,"Abu Dharr (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1662,"“When you make some soup, make a good amount by adding plenty of liquid, and give some to your neighbors.” Related by Muslim.",,,50779,"Abu Dharr (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1663,"“If anyone relieves a Muslim believer from one of the hardships of this worldly life, Allah will relieve him of one of the hardships of the Day of Resurrection. If anyone makes it easy for the one who is indebted to him (while finding it difficult to repay), Allah will make it easy for him in this worldly life and in the Hereafter, and if anyone conceals the faults of a Muslim, Allah will conceal his faults in this world and in the Hereafter. Allah helps His slave as long as he helps his brother.” Related by Muslim.",,,50780,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1664,"“He who guides (others) to an act of goodness, will have a reward similar to that of its doer.” Related by Muslim.",,,50781,"Ibn Mas'ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1665,"“If anyone seeks refuge in Allah’s name, grant him protection; if anyone asks you for something in Allah’s name give him something; and if anyone does you a favor recompense him, but if you do not have the means to do so, make Dua (supplication) for him.” Related by Al-Baihaqi.",,,50782,"Ibn Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1666,"An-Nu’man bin Bashir (RAA) narrated, I heard Allah‘s Messenger (ﷺ) saying, (Nu'man pointed with his two fingers to his ears) ‘Both lawful (Halal) and unlawful things (Haram) are evident but in between them there are doubtful things·and most people have no knowledge about them. So he, who saves himself from these doubtful things, saves his religion and his honor (i.e. keeps them blameless). And he who indulges in these doubtful things is like a shepherd who pastures (his animals) near the Hima (private pasture) of someone else and at any moment he is liable to get in it. (O people!) Beware! Every king has a Hima and the Hima of Allah on the earth is what He declared unlawful (Haram). Beware In the body there is a piece of flesh if it becomes sound and healthy, the whole body becomes sound and healthy but if it gets spoilt, the whole body gets spoilt and that is the heart.” Agreed upon.",,,50783,,Chapter 16
1667,"“Cursed is he, who is the slave of the Dinar, the slave of the Dirham, and the slave of the cloak bordered with silk. If he is given anything he would be satisfied, but if he is not given anything he is displeased.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50784,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1668,"Ibn 'Umar (RAA) narrated, ‘Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) took hold of my shoulders and said, “Be in this world as though you were a stranger or a passerby.” Ibn ’Umar used to say, “If you are alive in the evening, do not expect to be alive till the morning and if you are alive in the morning do not expect to be alive till the evening, and take from your health for your sickness, and from your life for your death.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50785,,Chapter 16
1669,“He who imitates any people (in their actions) is considered to be one of them.” Related by Abu Dawud and Ibn Hibban graded it as Sahih.,,,50786,"Ibn ’Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1670,"Ibn 'Abbas (RAA) narrated, ‘One day I was riding behind the Prophet when he said, “O lad, be mindful of Allah and He will protect you. Be mindful of Allah and you shall find Him with you. When you ask (for anything), ask it from Allah, and if you seek help, seek help from Allah.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who verified it as Hasan and Sahih.",,,50787,,Chapter 16
1671,"Sahl bin Sa'd (RAA) narrated, A man came to the Prophet and said, “O Allah`s Messenger (ﷺ), direct me to a deed which if I do it, I shall be loved by Allah and by people.” He replied, “If you practice abstinence in this world, Allah will love you, and if you abstain from (desiring) what people have, they will love you.” Related by Ibn Majah and others with a good chain of narrators.",,,50788,,Chapter 16
1672,"Sa'd bin Abi Waqqas (RAA) narrated, ‘l heard Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) saying, “Allah loves the pious rich maxim who is inconspicuous (free from showing off or hypocrisy).” Related by Muslim.",,,50789,,Chapter 16
1673,“A sign of man's good observance of Islam (his piety) is to keep away from that which does not concern him.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded it as Hadith Hasan.,,,50790,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1674,"“A human being has never filled any vessel which is worse than his own belly.” Related by At-Tirmidhi, who graded it to be Hasan.",,,50791,"Al-Miqdam bin Ma’diakrib (RAA), narrated that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1675,"“All the sons of Adam are sinners, but the best of sinners are those who repent often.” Related by At·Tirmidhi and Ibn Majah with a strong chain of narrators.",,,50792,"Anas (RAA) narrated that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1676,"“Keeping silent is considered as (an act of`) wisdom, but very few practice it.” Related by Al-Baihaqi in his book Shu'ab al-Iman with a weak chain of narrators a he deemed the sound view is that it is traced back to one of the companions who quoted it from Luqman Al-Hakim.",,,50793,"Anas (RAA) narrated that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1677,"“Avoid envy, for envy devours good deeds just as fire devours firewood.” Related by Abu Dawud.",,,50794,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1678,Ibn Majah related a similar hadith on the authority of Anas.,,,50795,,Chapter 16
1679,“The strong man is not the good wrestler; but the strong man is he who controls himself when he is angry.” Agreed upon.,,,50796,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1680,“Oppression will turn into darkness on the Day of Resurrection.” Agreed upon.,,,50797,"Ibn 'Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1681,"“Beware of oppression, for oppression will turn into excessive darkness on the Day of Resurrection and beware of niggardliness, for niggardliness destroyed your predecessors.” Related by Muslim.",,,50798,"Jabir bin 'Abdullah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1682,"“The thing I fear most for you is the lesser shirk (polytheism), showing-off (of good deeds).” Related by Ahmad with a good chain of narrators,",,,50799,"Mahmud bin Labid (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1683,"“There are three signs of a hypocrite: when he speaks, he tells lies; when he makes a promise, he breaks it; and when he is entrusted, he betrays his trust.” Agreed upon.",,,50800,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1684,"Al·Bukhari and Muslim reported another hadith on the authority of ’Abdullah bin ’Umar (RAA) with the addition, “and when he quarrels, he is abusive (behaves in a very impudent and insulting manner).”",,,50801,,Chapter 16
1685,"insulting a Muslim is disobedience to Allah, and fighting with him is Kufr (disbelief).” Agreed upon.",,,50802,"Ibn Mas'ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1686,"“Avoid suspicion, for suspicion is the most false form of talk.” Agreed upon.",,,50803,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1687,"Ma'qil bin Yasar (RAA) narrated, ‘I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) saying, “Any governor in charge of Muslim subjects who dies while acting dishonestly towards them will be excluded by Allah from Paradise.” Agreed upon.",,,50804,,Chapter 16
1688,"“O Allah, cause distress to him who has any charge over my people and causes them distress.” Related by Muslim.",,,50805,"‘A’ishah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1689,"“When any of you fights, he must avoid (striking) the face.” Agreed upon.",,,50806,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1690,"“Do not get angry.” The man repeated that several times and he replied, “Do not get angry.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50807,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated, ‘A man said, “O Messenger of Allah, advise me.” The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1691,"“Some men acquire Allah’s Property (such as the funds of the Muslim state treasury, Zakah etc.) and they will go to Hell on the Day of Resurrection.” Related Al-Bukhari.",,,50808,"Khawlah al-Ansariyah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1692,"Abu Dharr (RAA) quoted the Prophet (ﷺ) saying among what he narrated from Allah, the Most High that He has said, “O MY slaves, I have made oppression unlawful for myself and I have made it unlawful among you, so do not oppress one another.” Related by Muslim.",,,50809,,Chapter 16
1693,“If what you say about him is true you have backbitten him and if it is not true you have slandered him.” Related by Muslim.,,,50810,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) asked, “Do you know what backbiting is?” They replied, `Allah and His Messenger (ﷺ) know best.’ He said, “It is saying something about your brother which he dislikes.” Someone asked, ‘Supposing that what I said about my brother was true?’ and the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1694,"“Avoid jealousy between yourselves, do not outbid one another (with a view to raising the price), do not harbor hatred against one another, do not bear enmity against one another, one of you should not enter into a transaction when the other has already entered into it; and be fellow brothers and slaves of Allah. A Muslim is a Muslim’s brother. He does not wrong, desert or despise him. Piety is found here (pointing three times to his chest), despising his Muslim brother is enough evil for any man to do. Every Muslim’s blood, property and honor are unlawful to be violated by another Muslim.” Related by Muslim.",,,50811,"Abu Hurairah [RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1695,"Qutbah bin Malik (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to say, “O Allah, I seek refuge in you from evil morals, deeds, passions and diseases.” Related by At-Tirmidhi. Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih and it is his version.",,,50812,,Chapter 16
1696,“Don’t dispute with your brother; don’t make jokes with him; and don’t make him a promise which you would break.” Related by At-Tirmidhi with a weak chain of narrators.,,,50813,"Ibn ’Abbas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1697,“There are two characteristics which are not combined in a believer; miserliness and bad morals.” Related by At-Tirmidhi with a weakness in its chain of narrators.,,,50814,"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri (RAA), narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1698,"“When two men insult one another, what they say is mainly the fault of the one who began it, so long as the one who is oppressed does not transgress.” Related by Muslim.",,,50815,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1699,"“He who causes harm to a Muslim will be harmed by Allah, and he who acts in a hostile manner against a Muslim, will be punished in the same way by Allah.” Related by Abu Dawud and At-Tirmidhi who graded it to be Hasan (good).",,,50816,"Abu Sirmah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1700,“Allah hates the profligate and the obscene.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded it to be Sahih.,,,50817,"Abu ad-Darda (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1701,"“The believer is not a slanderer, nor does he curse others, and nor is he immoral or shameless.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded it to be Hasan. Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih and Ad-Daraqutni said that it is most probably Mawquf (traced only to a Companion).",,,50818,"At-Tirmidhi also related on the authority of Ibn Mas'ud (RAA) that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1702,"“Avoid reviling the dead, they have already seen the result of (the deeds) that they forwarded before them.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50819,"A’ishah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1703,“A backbiter will not enter Paradise.” Agreed upon.,,,50820,"Hudhaifah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1704,"“If one restrained his anger, Allah will keep His punishment from him (on the Day of Resurrection).” Related by At-Tabarani in al-Awsat.",,,50821,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1705,The aforementioned hadith is supported by a narration on the authority of Ibn ’Umar related by Ibn Abi Ad-Dunia.,,,50822,,Chapter 16
1706,"“A crafty person, a miser and one who badly treats those under his authority will not enter Paradise.” Related by At-Tirmidhi in two separate traditions and there is a weakness in its chain of narrators.",,,50823,"Abu Bakr as-Siddiq (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1707,"“If anyone listened to the talk of some people, when they do not like him to do that, then molten led will be poured into his ears on the Day of Resurrection.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50824,"Ibn ’Abbas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1708,“Blessed is he who is preoccupied with his defects rather than those of other people.” Related by Al-Bazzar with a good chain of narrators.,,,50825,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1709,“Whoever exalts himself and walks proudly; Allah will be angry with him when he meets Him (on the Day of Resurrection).” Related Al-Hakim with a reliable chain of narrators.,,,50826,"Ibn 'Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1710,“Haste comes from Satan.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded is as Hasan.,,,50827,"Sahl bin Sa’d (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1711,“Pessimism is part of bad character.” Related by Ahmad with a weak chain of narrators.,,,50828,"'A'ishah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1712,“Men accustomed to cursing will not be intercessors or witnesses on the Day of Resurrection.” Related by Muslim.,,,50829,"Abu ad-Darda’ (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1713,"“If anyone disgraces his brother for a sin, he will not die before committing it himself.” Related At-Tirmidhi who graded it to be Hasan.",,,50830,"Mu'adh bin Jabal (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1714,"“Woe to him who lies in his talk to make the people laugh, Woe to him! Woe to him!” Related by the three Imams with a strong chain of narrators.",,,50831,"Bahz bin Hakim narrated on the authority of his father, on the authority of his grandfather (RAA) that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1715,“The atonement of backbiting a man is to ask Allah to forgive him.” Related by Al-Harith bin Abu Usamah with a weak chain of narrators.,,,50832,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1716,“The most despicable amongst people in the sight of Allah is the ruthless argumentative (person).” Related by Muslim.,,,50833,"'A’ishah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1717,"“Adhere (you people) to truth, for truth leads to good deeds and good deeds lead to Paradise, and if a man continues to speak the truth and makes truth his object he will be recorded as truthful before Allah. Avoid (you people) falsehood, for falsehood leads to wickedness and wickedness leads to Hell, and if a man continues to speak falsehood and makes falsehood his object he will be recorded as a liar before Allah.” Agreed upon.",,,50834,"Ibn Mas'ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1718,"“Beware of suspicion, for suspicion amounts to the worst form of lying.” Agreed upon.",,,50835,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1719,"“Avoid sitting by the road side.” The people then said, ‘O Allah‘s Messenger (ﷺ), we cannot do without those meeting places in which we converse” So he said, “Well, if you insist (on that) give the road its due rights.” They asked, ‘What are the road’s due rights?’ He replied, “Lowering your gaze, abstaining from anything offensive, returning salutations, enjoining the right (Ma'ruf) and forbidding from evil deeds (Munkar).” Agreed upon.",,,50836,"Abu Said al-Khudri (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1720,"“When Allah wishes good for anyone, He bestows upon him the Fiqh (comprehension) of the religion.” Agreed upon.",,,50837,"Mu’awiyah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1721,“The heaviest thing which will be put on the believer’s scale (on the Day of Resurrection) will be good morals.” Related by Abu Dawud and At-Tirmidhi who graded it as Sahih.,,,50838,"Abu ad-Darda’ (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1722,"“Haya (modesty, bashfulness etc.) is a part of Faith.” Agreed upon.",,,50839,"Ibn 'Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1723,"“One of the things people have learned from the words of the earliest prophecies is, “If you don’t feel any shame, do whatever you like.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50840,"Ibn Mas’ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1724,"“A believer who is strong (and healthy) is better and dearer to Allah than the weak believer, but there is goodness in both of them. Be keen on what benefits you and seek help from Allah, and do not give up. If anything afflicts you do not say, ‘If I had done such and such things, such and such would have happened.’ But say, ‘Allah decrees and what He wills He does,’ for (the utterance) ‘If I had’ provides an opening for the deeds of the devil.” Related by Muslim.",,,50841,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1725,"“Allah, the Most High has revealed to me that you (people) should be humble, so that no one transgresses another, or boasts to the other.” Related by Muslim.",,,50842,"’Iyad bin Himar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1726,"“If a Muslim defends his brother’s honor in his absence, Allah will protect his face from the fire of Hell on the Day of Resurrection.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded it to be Hasan.",,,50843,"Abu ad-Darda’ (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1727,Ahmad related a similar hadith on the authority of Asma the daughter of Yazid.,,,50844,,Chapter 16
1728,“Sadaqah does not decrease property and Allah increases the honor of him who forgives and no one will humble himself for Allah’s sake except that Allah raises his status.” Related by Muslim.,,,50845,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1729,"“O people, extend greetings (saying Salam to each other), keep relations with your kin, provide food (to people) and pray at night when people are asleep and you will enter Paradise in peace.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded it as Sahih.",,,50846,"'Abdullah bin Salam (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1730,"“The religion is Nasihah.” the people said, ‘To whom should it be directed?’ He replied, “To Allah, His Book, His Messenger (ﷺ), to the leaders of the Muslims and to the common folk of the Muslims.” Related by Muslim.",,,50847,"Tamim ad-Dari (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1731,“The fear of Allah and good morals (Akhlaq) are the two major characteristics which lead to Paradise.” Related by At-Tirmidhi and Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih.,,,50848,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1732,"“You (people) cannot satisfy people with your wealth, but satisfy them with your cheerful faces and good morals.” Related by Abu Ya’la and Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih.",,,50849,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1733,“Every believer is the mirror of his brother.” Related by Abu Dawud with a good chain of narrators.,,,50850,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1734,“A believer who mixes with people and endures their annoyance is better than the one who does not mix with them and does not endure their annoyance.” Related by Ibn Majah with a good chain of narrators. At-Tirmidhi reported the hadith without mentioning the Companion.,,,50851,"Ibn ’Umar (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1735,"Ibn Mas’ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) Said, “O Allah You have made my creation perfect, so make my moral characteristics also be the best.”",,,50852,,Chapter 16
1736,"“Allah, the Most High says: ‘l am with my slave when he remembers me and his lips move with my mention.” Related by Ibn Majah and Ibn Hibban graded it as Sahih.",,,50853,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1737,“A man does nothing to rescue himself from Allah’s punishment better than remembering Allah.” Related by Ibn Abi Shaibah and At-Tabarani with a good chain of narrators.,,,50854,"Mu’adh Ibn Jabal (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1738,"“People will not sit in an assembly in which they remember Allah without the angels surrounding them, mercy covering them, and Allah mentioning them among those who are with Him.” Related by Muslim.",,,50855,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1739,“If people sit in an assembly in which they do not remember Allah or invoke blessings on the Prophet it will be a cause of grief to them on the Day of Resurrection.” Related by At-Tirmidhi who graded it as Hasan.,,,50856,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1740,"“Whoever says ten times: ‘None has the right to be worshipped except Allah alone, without partner, to Him belongs all sovereignty and praise. He gives life and causes death. He is over all things, Omnipotent will have a reward equivalent to that of emancipating four of the descendants of lsma'il from slavery.” Agreed upon.",,,50857,"Abu Aiyub al-Ansari (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1741,"“Whoever says a hundred times, ‘How perfect Allah is and I praise Him,’ his sins will be forgiven though they may be as much as the foam of the sea.” Agreed upon.",,,50858,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1742,"‘How perfect Allah is and I praise Him by the amount of His creation and His pleasure, and by the weight of His throne, and the ink of His words.” Related by Muslim.",,,50859,"Juairiyah bint al-Harith (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said to me, “Since leaving you have said four phrases which if weighed against all you have said today, would prove to be heavier:",Chapter 16
1743,"“The lasting good deeds are: (the saying of) ‘None has the right to be worshipped except Allah alone, How perfect Allah is and Allah is great and all praise is for Allah, There is no might nor power except with Allah.” Related by An-Nasa’i. Ibn Hibban and Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih.",,,50860,"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1744,"“The words dearer to Allah are four: ‘How perfect Allah is and all praise is for Allah. None has the right to be worshipped except Allah alone and Allah is great It does not matter which you say first.” Related by Muslim.",,,50861,"Samurah bin Jundub (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1745,"Abu Musa al-Ash'ari (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said to me, “O 'Abdullah bin Qais, would you like to be guided to one of the treasures of Paradise.” l here is no might nor power except with Allah.’ Agreed upon.",,,50862,,Chapter 16
1746,"An-Nasa’i added in his version, “there is no refuge from Allah except by turning to Him.’",,,50863,,Chapter 16
1747,"“Verily supplication is worship.” Related by the four Imams and At-Tirmidhi graded it as Sahih,",,,50864,"An-Nu’man bin al-Bashir (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1748,“Supplication is the pith of worship.” Related by At-Tirmidhi with a full chain of narrators.,,,50865,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1749,“Nothing is more honorable before Allah than supplication.” Related by At-Tirmidhi with a full chain of narrators. Ibn Hibban and Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih;.,,,50866,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1750,"“A supplication made between the Adhan and Iqamah is never rejected.” Related by An-Nasa’i and others, Ibn Hibban and others graded it as Sahih.",,,50867,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1751,"“Your Rabb (Lord of the Universe) is Modest and Generous, and would never turn the hands of a slave without gain when he raises them to Him (in supplication).” Related by the four lmams except An-Nasa’i. Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih.",,,50868,"Salman (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1752,"'Umar (RAA) narrated, ‘When the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) raised his hands in supplication, he did not lower them till he wiped his face with them.’ Related by At-Tirmidhi.",,,50869,,Chapter 16
1753,"The Hadith narrated by Ibn ’Abbas (RAA) related by Abu Dawud and others. Put together, they confirm that it is Hasan.",,,50870,"There are other traditions, which support this narration, of which is:",Chapter 16
1754,“Those who are nearest to me on the Day of Resurrection are those who invoke many blessings on me.” Related by At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Hibban graded it as Sahih.,,,50871,"Ibn Mas'ud (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1755,"“The best manner of asking for forgiveness is to say: “O Allah! You are my Lord. None has the right to be worshipped except You. You created me and I am your servant and I abide by your covenant and promise as best I can. I seek refuge in you from the evil, which I have committed. I acknowledge your favor upon me and I acknowledge my sins, so forgive me, for verily none can forgive sin except you.” Related by Al-Bukhari.",,,50872,"Shaddad bin Aus (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
1756,"“O Allah! I ask you for pardon and well-being in my religious and worldly affairs, and my family and my wealth. O Allah! Cover my weaknesses and set at ease my dismay. O Allah! Preserve me from the front and from behind and on my right and on my left and from above, and I seek refuge with you lest I be swallowed up by the earth.” Related by An-Nasa’i and Ibn Majah. Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih.",,,50873,"Ibn ’Umar (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) never failed to say these words in the morning and the evening:",Chapter 16
1757,"Ibn 'Umar (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to supplicate saying, “O Allah! I seek refuge in you from the withholding of your favor, the decline of the good health you have given, the suddenness of your vengeance and from all forms of your wrath.” Related by Muslim.",,,50874,,Chapter 16
1758,"Ibn Umar (RAA) narrated, “The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to say, “O Allah! I seek refuge in you from the burden of debts and from being over-powered by men and from the gloating of enemies (at an evil I am afflicted with).” Related by",,,50875,,Chapter 16
1759,"‘O Allah! I ask you by virtue that I testify that you are Allah; there is no God but You, the one —· the Self Sufficient Master, Who did not beget, and was not begotten, and to whom no one is equal.’ Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) then said, “He has asked Allah by His Name by which when asked, He gives, and by which when supplicated, He answers.” Related by the four Imams and Ibn Hibban graded it as Sahih.",,,50876,"Buraidah (RAA) narrated, ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) heard a man saying:",Chapter 16
1760,“and to you do we return.” Related by the four Imams.,,,50877,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated, ‘Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) would say in the morning, “O Allah! By Your leave we have reached the morning and by your leave we have reached the evening. By Your leave we live and die. Unto you is our resurrection.” In the evening, he would say the same except the last phrase:",Chapter 16
1761,"“O our Lord, grants us the best in this life and the best in the next life, and protects us from the punishment of the Fire.” Agreed upon.",,,50878,"Anas (RAA) narrated, “The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to supplicate frequently:",Chapter 16
1762,"Abu Musa al-Ash’ari (RAA) narrated, “The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to supplicate, “O Allah, forgive me my faults, my ignorance, my immoderation in my concern. And you are better aware (of my affairs) than myself. O Allah, grant me forgiveness (of the faults which I committed) seriously or otherwise (and which I committed) inadvertently and deliberately. All these (failings) are in me. O Allah, grant me forgiveness from the faults, which I did in haste or deferred, which I committed in privacy or in public and you are better aware (of them) than myself. You are the First and the Last and over all things you are Omnipotent.” Agreed Upon.",,,50879,,Chapter 16
1763,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to say, “O Allah! Set right for me my religion, which is the safeguard of my affairs. And set right for me the affairs of the world wherein is my living. Decree the Hereafter to be good for me. And make this life, for me, (a source) of abundance for every good and make my death (a source) of comfort to me and protection against every evil.” Related by Muslim.",,,50880,,Chapter 16
1764,"Anas (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to say, “O Allah! Grant me benefit in what you have taught me, and teach me useful knowledge and provide me with knowledge that will benefit me.” Related by An-Nasa’i and Al-Hakim.",,,50881,,Chapter 16
1765,"At-Tirmidhi reported a similar tradition on the authority of `Abu Hurairah (RAA), he said at its end, “And increase my knowledge. Praise be to Allah in all circumstances. I seek refuge in Allah from the state of those who will go to Hell.” Its chain of narrators is good.",,,50882,,Chapter 16
1766,"’A’ishah (RAA) narrated, ‘Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) taught her this supplication, “O Allah! I ask you of all good of what I have done and what I have not done in this world and in the Hereafter. I seek refuge in you from the evil of what I have done and what I have not done in this world and in the Hereafter. O Allah! I ask of you all good that your servant and Prophet Muhammad (ﷺ) used to ask of you. I seek refuge in you from all evil that your servant and Prophet Muhammad used to seek refuge in you from. O Allah! I ask you for Paradise and what brings me nearer to it of deeds and sayings. I seek refuge in You from Hell-Fire and what brings me near to it of deeds and sayings. I ask you for the good consequences of Your Decree.” Related by Ibn Majah Ibn Hibban and Al-Hakim graded it as Sahih",,,50883,,Chapter 16
1767,"“Two phrases which are dear to the Compassionate One and are light on the tongue but heavy in the scale are: “How perfect Allah is and I praise Him; and How perfect Allah is the Most Great.” Agreed upon.",,,50884,"Abu Hurairah (RAA) narrated that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:",Chapter 16
